SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1780085153
OL,3,CCross-examination of alleged victim
OL,4,Ccontinues in Jeffrey Donaldson trial
OL,6,FThe barrister said the complainant
OL,7,F"would have known what he was doing to
OL,8,Fyou was wrong".
OL,10,FShe said: "Not necessarily, abuse is a
OL,11,Fvery complicated thing."
OL,13,FThe barrister asked her if she was
OL,14,Fsuggesting she had not known until she
OL,15,Fwas an adult that what she claimed had
OL,16,Fhappened to her was wrong.
OL,18,FShe responded: "I began to piece
OL,19,Ftogether factually there were things
OL,20,Fthat happened as normal that I should
OL,21,Fnot have accepted as normal practice."
OL,26,@oD@AOUpD@NO]rD@KOUsD@XO]zD@POU}D@fO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
