PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1780085153
OL,3,CCross-examination of alleged victim
OL,4,Ccontinues in Jeffrey Donaldson trial
OL,6,FThe barrister then referred to an
OL,7,Fincident where the woman had claimed
OL,8,FDonaldson had "perched" over the top
OL,9,Fof her, using a light to look at her
OL,10,F"private parts".
OL,12,FShe was challenged about her account,
OL,13,Fwith Mr Vaughan saying: "I suggest
OL,14,Fthat is not true."
OL,16,FThe barrister added: "You were
OL,17,Fconfused and you were not sure of what
OL,18,Fyou had seen."
OL,20,FShe said: "To this day I am still
OL,21,Fconfused... I am honest about that."
OL,26,@pD@OOUpD@WO]rD@AOUrD@OO]uD@YOUvD@RO]xD@
